habit_change: My first foray into music was listening to heavy amounts of EDM, this was during the end of my midle school years and the beginning of my high school years. My friend groups started putting on hip hop artists like Fetty Wap and Lil Uzi Vert whenever we would hang out so I slowly started to incorporate those acts into my music selections, but still mainlining EDM music. It was only when I got to college when hip hop started to majorly take over my listening habits, but I still tossed in more mellow EDM tracks and a lot of classical music as I mellowed out more overall as a person. My college friends also introduced me to a lot of artists from different genres as well and I got more explorational with my listening habits, which led me to adopting a slew of new and interesting artists over an assortment of genres. About a couple days ago as of the writing of this survey entry, I revisited a lot of artists that I used to listen to in middle school that I dropped and I've started to relisten to their tracks a lot more.
habits_overall: I mainly listen to hip hop or EDM, but I also tend to stay on the same five to ten tracks that I most recently have found and I will continuosly listen to those until I get bored of them and dive back into my musical library for other tracks.

Post pandemic I work alone at a desk and usually just listen to things I already know on headphones.
